comments.body:
@aplavin They are not official rules, but I feel perfectly fine with leaving a blocking comment on registrations that do not meet what I consider reasonable standards. Any member of the community is free to do the same.

None of it is a registration _requirement_. Any registry maintainer can override blocking comments. We really have almost no absolute, hard requirements for registration. Only guidelines, and I believe that all of my points are in the spirit of those guidelines.

[noblock]
